Youre Eldership is not for this tyme and state, as it is before declared, and yet maye menne bée compelled to render a reason of their faythe if any be doubted of: althoughe youre places quoted for that purpose proue no suche thing. For Paule the .1. to the Corinth. 11. vse. 28. willeth a man to examine himselfe before he eate of that breade. &c. and not to be examined of any other. Peter. 1. Epist. cha. 3 vs. 15. willeth euery christian man to be redy without fear in time of persecution, to render a reason or defence (for the Greke is 
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  ) of his fayth, & not at all tymes to euery man, as maister Caluine him selfe noteth vppon that place.
